<?xml version="1.0"?>
<page xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" layout="admin-1column" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:magento:framework:View/Layout/etc/page_configuration.xsd">
    <update handle="editor"/>
    <body>
        <referenceContainer name="content">
            <!-- <block class="Ahmed\Jobs\Block\Adminhtml\Department\Edit" name="Ahmed_Jobs_Name" /> --> <!-- template="Ahmed_Jobs::block_name.phtml" -->             
            <uiComponent name="jobs_department_form"/>
        </referenceContainer>
    </body>
</page>

<!--
Render flow for the legacy admin edit form:

1. The layout handle jobs_department_edit.xml adds the main container block:
   Ahmed\Jobs\Block\Adminhtml\Department\Edit

2. That block extends Magento\Backend\Block\Widget\Form\Container.
   It renders the admin form wrapper: title, Back/Reset/Save buttons, and form area.

3. During layout preparation, Form\Container::_prepareLayout() creates a child block named "form"
   using _blockGroup + _controller + _mode:
   Ahmed_Jobs + adminhtml_department + edit + Form
   => Ahmed\Jobs\Block\Adminhtml\Department\Edit\Form

4. The container template calls:
   $block->getFormHtml()

5. Form\Container::getFormHtml() sets the save URL on the child form block:
   getChildBlock('form')->setData('action', getSaveUrl())

6. Then the child form block is rendered.

7. Before rendering, Magento\Backend\Block\Widget\Form::_beforeToHtml() calls:
   _prepareForm()

8. Our Edit\Form::_prepareForm() creates the form object with FormFactory,
   adds the fieldset and fields, fills values from the registered model,
   then calls setForm($form).

9. The form object finally renders the HTML <form> and its fields.
-->

